[[span class="st" style="color: #D7BA89"]]SPECIAL CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES:[[/span]] See [[span class="st" style="color: #D7BA89"]]Addendum 9338.III[[/span]].

[[span class="st" style="color:#D7BA89"]]DESCRIPTION:[[/span]] SCP-9338 is, in its current form, an indestructible,[[footnote]]Under the Sa-Pan definition, proposed in //Fundamental Properties in a Paratechnological Context// (Pan & Sa, 2013).[[/footnote]] static, cuboid block of wood, measuring 50cm x 80cm x 120cm.[[footnote]]Most of the time.[[/footnote]] While impossible to sample, the majority of experts have agreed the wood belongs to the species //pinus tabuliformis// var. //tabuliformis//.[[footnote]]Notably, this species is not native to Singapore, where SCP-9338 was discovered.[[/footnote]] Apart from its indestructibility, SCP-9338 exhibits identical physical traits to any other cuboid of wood of the same presumed species.

[[span class="st" style="color:#D7BA89"]]HISTORY:[[/span]] SCP-9338 was discovered on the 12th of March, 2020, at geographical location {{1°23'28.5"N 103°58'49.8"E}}. Its original form differed greatly from its current one:
[[div class="blockquote"]]
[[span class="st" style="color:black"]]DESCRIPTION:[[/span]] SCP-9338 is an anomalously, impenetrably dense forested area spanning an estimated 150 square meters. It comprises trees of the species //pinus tabuliformis// var. //tabuliformis//, but the exact number is impossible to ascertain; both visual and technological scans appear to "get lost" within the area. The trees, while not individually impervious to destruction, exhibit a collective resilience to eradication efforts; each time a tree is destroyed, cut down, or otherwise damaged, the area anomalously shifts to produce a new, whole tree to replace it.
[[/div]]

Initially discovered by civilians ghost-hunting in the nearby Old Changi Hospital,[[footnote]]Relevant video has been scrubbed from the internet by Site-512 IT. Relevant individuals have been amnesticised.[[/footnote]] **MTF-ꙟ-1** was deployed for the initial investigation, which preliminarily classified the anomaly as **SAFE**/**DARK**/**NOTICE**.[[footnote]]Risk class was later changed to **CAUTION** by EL&R.[[/footnote]] A temporary cordon was placed around SCP-9338. For further information on the investigation history of SCP-9338, refer to [[span class="st" style="color: #D7BA89"]]Addendum 9338.I[[/span]].

------

