[[span class="st" style="color: #D7BA89"]]Addendum 9338.III:[[/span]] ConProc Proposal 9338:01, active Special Containment Procedures for SCP-9338[[footnote]]Never formalised, due to formatting and readability issues.[[/footnote]]

[[div class="document"]]

+ CONPROC PROPOSAL 9338:01

[[div style="text-align: right; font-size: 0.9em; font-style: italic"]]
19/07/20
Dr. Tabitha Theophilia Tay
Senior Researcher (Logics), Esoteric Logics & Ritualistics, Site-512
[[/div]]
------

[[span class="st"]]PROPOSED SPECIAL CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES:[[/span]] SCP-9338 is to be temporarily held by EL&R. It is to be kept away from other blocks of wood. It is to be kept near to a piece of pure jade at all times. There must be at least two specialists from EL&R on standby to respond to any incidents involving SCP-9338. It is to be stored in the centre of a sufficiently large space (at least 150 square meters).

SCP-9338 shall be treated as follows in different forms:
- When in the form of **wood**, it is to be treated as a low-threat anomaly, isolated in accordance with the above procedures.
- When in the form of **forest**, one tree is to be carefully and deliberately removed by one of the above trained specialists. This will regress it to the form of **wood**. The removed tree may be burned after.
- When in the form of **dense forest**, or its original form, one tree is to be carefully and deliberately removed by one of the trained specialists, prioritising whichever tree in reach is perceived as the highest. This will regress it to the form of **forest**. The removed tree may be burned after.
- When in the form of **forest** or **dense forest**, where the above attempts fail, the piece of pure jade is to be carefully and deliberately added by one of the trained specialists, inserted from the perceived left of the anomaly. If in the form of **dense forest**, specialists are advised to watch for falling wood. If this succeeds, it will enter the form of **beautiful jade**.
- If the above fails, or if it enters the form of **beautiful jade**, EL&R leadership is to be notified immediately. A designated verbivore[[footnote]]Undefined.[[/footnote]] is to be deployed.
[[/div]]

------

[[span class="st" style="color: #D7BA89"]]Addendum 9338.IV:[[/span]] Proposed additional description for  SCP-9338[[footnote]]Do not attempt to propose this again.[[/footnote]]

[[div class="blockquote"]]
[[span class="st" style="color:black"]]DESCRIPTION:[[/span]] [..]

SCP-9338 is, to be more precise, the Chinese bound morpheme 木 //mù//. In its base state, it is highly unstable, due to its lack of inherently stabilised meaning; fortunately (or unfortunately), it defaults to the generic understanding of 木块 (wooden block).[[footnote]]Perhaps this has to do with the visual perception of the word 木 as something small and non-complex.[[/footnote]]

This high instability manifests in its propensity to collapse //upwards// into the simplest single-character morpheme that takes 木 as a root, 林 (forest). In the form of the forest, it is trivially reduced to its base state via figurative removal of the excess 木. The unstable faux-morpheme decays quickly into the significantly-stable meaning-base 树 (tree), and can be safely burned.[[footnote]]The faux-morpheme's decay, as opposed to the pure morpheme's collapse, is best understood as a result of the pure morpheme's preference to stay in a stem most aligned with the root, disregarding the stability of the result.[[/footnote]]

In around 24.1% of cases,[[footnote]]Empirically estimated.[[/footnote]] SCP-9338 is carried forward by semantic momentum and collapses further upwards into the next simplest single-character morpheme, 森 (dense forest). At this juncture, figurative removal of the excess 木 results in the production of two 树. Aiming for the perceptually "higher" one reduces the risk of crush.[[footnote]]So far, only two incidents have occurred, both non-lethal. Of course, failing to remove the upper 木 still results in regression to 林, but instead of a clean un-densing, half of the morpheme collapses on top of you.[[/footnote]]

It is theorised that the careful application of jade (玉) will be sufficient to collapse SCP-9338 into beautiful jade (琳). This will only be applied as a last resort, as 琳 is a morpheme far less stable than the base 木;[[footnote]]In modern Chinese, 琳 is found almost exclusively in names; its base meaning is rarely used.[[/footnote]] any collapse from it will have catastrophic results.[[footnote]]Hence, deployment of the verbivore.[[/footnote]]

[[/div]]

------

[[span class="st" style="color: #D7BA89"]]Addendum 9338.V:[[/span]] Selected RAISA Response

[[div class="blockquote"]]
RAISA cannot accept this description. There's practically zero connection between the claims made about the skip and its discernable, measurable physical characteristics; the language used does not hit any standard of formality; nor does it operate even marginally within the boundaries of accepted anomalous science. Also, what the fuck is a verbivore?[[footnote]]The thing to be deployed.[[/footnote]]
[[/div]]

